The paper deals with the problem of guided depth map super-resolution, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also mentions the use of residual dense networks, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
